<br>
As for warriors, I think there was a minor nerf that affected them due to taunting ability of procs on weapons and stuff.  They were already complaining about taunt not being enough.  It is funny what you see on msg boards.  Someone made a very intelligent argument about the taunt skill, and how intelligent creatures aren't going to ignor the row of 8 wizards int he back casting huge ass DD and AE spells on them because the tank is calling him names.  Makes much sense. <br>
<br>
Also, class envy posts everywhere.  What people don't realize is enhancements to a class helps the group.  Not everyone is going to stop being a warrior cause paladins were given new abilities.  Heh, on one board there was a suggestion, no word of a lie:<br>
<br>
Silly_Warrior says, &quot;We should have an ability called Second Wind.  This would be exactly like the paladin ability Lay on Hands except it is a complete heal which is better because paladins don't do complete heals.  I mean with all the new abilities they get we DESERVE this.&quot;<br>
<br>
/boggle<br>
<br>
Ah well, my advice, stay away from class msg boards unless you need help and advice.  And don't give into their BS either.  I have before.  I now actually only go to one other board than VF and SV boards and that is a decent warrior one with only a few bitch fests.  Easily avoidable.  I am not saying avoid them like the plague, but if you see they complain about hteir class lots don't go there.  At first it seems silly, but after a while it gets to ya.  <br>
<br>
If you have fun playing a class gotta play it and ignore the disadvantages and stuff.  As a group we compliment each other and make up for htem and will always be there to group and go on raids with each other.<br>
<br>
